  {%- comment -%} ===== LEAD ===== {%- endcomment -%}
  <h2 class="advertorial__subheadline">If You've Ever Bought a Pain Product at 2 AM, This Is for You</h2>

  <p class="advertorial__text">I know the cycle. You can't sleep. The pain is grinding. You grab your phone and start searching.</p>

  <p class="advertorial__text">You find something with great reviews. Your heart beats faster. You think <em>this one's different.</em> You order it. It arrives. Day one feels promising. <strong>By day five, the pain is exactly where it was.</strong></p>

  <p class="advertorial__text">Then it goes in the drawer.</p>

  <p class="advertorial__text">I rode that cycle for three years. Eleven products. Same result every time.</p>

  <p class="advertorial__text"><strong>But here's what nobody told me — and what changed everything:</strong></p>

  <p class="advertorial__text advertorial__text--highlight">I wasn't picking the wrong products. I was picking products that all shared the same hidden limitation.</p>

