  {%- comment -%} ===== BACKGROUND STORY ===== {%- endcomment -%}
  <h2 class="advertorial__subheadline">My Breaking Point Was a Wednesday Afternoon</h2>

  <p class="advertorial__text">It wasn't dramatic. No hospital. No emergency.</p>

  <p class="advertorial__text">I was unloading the dishwasher. I got through the top rack fine. Then I bent down for the bottom rack.</p>

  <p class="advertorial__text"><strong>The pain hit so fast my vision went white.</strong></p>

  <p class="advertorial__text">I grabbed the counter. Stood there shaking for two minutes. Left the rest and sat in my recliner.</p>

  <p class="advertorial__text">When my husband came home, I told him the dishwasher just finished running.</p>

  <p class="advertorial__text">He knew I was lying. I knew he knew. Neither of us said a word.</p>

  <p class="advertorial__text">That silence broke something in me. I used to cook Sunday dinners for twelve people. Now I couldn't bend down to a dishwasher.</p>

