  <p class="advertorial__text">Here's what I wish a doctor had told me three years ago:</p>

  <p class="advertorial__text"><strong>Heating pads?</strong> They warm your skin. Your skin isn't the problem. The second you remove it, the relief vanishes — because it never reached the tissue underneath.</p>

