  <p class="advertorial__text"><strong>TENS units?</strong> They distract your nerves temporarily. Turn it off and the pain floods right back. It was always there. You just couldn't feel it for twenty minutes.</p>

  <p class="advertorial__text"><strong>Cortisone shots?</strong> They work — temporarily. My first one lasted eight weeks. My third lasted ten days. Diminishing returns, $1,400 a pop.</p>

  <p class="advertorial__text">None of these fail because they're bad products. <strong>They fail because they can't physically reach where chronic pain originates.</strong></p>

